law.text:
The council shall cooperate with the Cabinet for Economic Development and with wood products industries applying for economic revitalization and development project inducements for the following purposes:
To analyze the impacts of an applicant's projects on forest productivity and watershed protection;
To develop a comprehensive program that addresses those impacts in the proposed procurement area through the appropriate use of:
Best management practices as established in Kentucky Forest Practices Guidelines published by the Division of Forestry of the Department for Natural Resources;
Logger education, training, and contracting programs;
Forest stewardship and other assistance programs for landowners; and
Ground water protection plans; and
To develop measures to ensure that the program developed for the procurement area becomes an integral part of the applicant's plan.
